<subSubSection box="[151,958,151,177]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,958,151,177]" box="[151,958,151,177]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,958,151,177]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
Key to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1897" box="[287,424,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[287,424,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Neurotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of the Russian Far East and Korea
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="key">
<key pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyStep pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[151,753,220,242]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,163,220,241]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">1</emphasis>
(a) Head covered with long hairs (
<figureCitation box="[543,603,220,242]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 1a,b; 2b; 2bb).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,810,249,271]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(b) Occipital carina blunt or inconspicuous (
<figureCitation box="[638,697,249,271]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 1a, b). ... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[798,810,249,270]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">2</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[151,1235,279,301]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
– (aa) Head glabrous or nearly so except for sparsely pilose gena and clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[941,1001,279,301]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 1aa, bb; 4a, b–5bb, cc).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,762,308,330]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(bb) Occipital carina sharply defined (
<figureCitation box="[568,627,308,330]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 1aa, bb). ... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[750,762,308,329]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">3</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[151,192,337,359]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,192,337,359]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">2(1)</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,628,367,389]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">(a) Abdomen without distinct bluish luster.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,909,396,418]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(b) Female: clypeus with large creamy white mark medially (
<figureCitation box="[800,860,396,418]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 2b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,676,425,447]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(c) Male: head entirely black. ... 
<taxonomicName box="[528,616,426,447]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Acantholyda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[528,616,426,447]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">N. atrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 58
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[151,680,455,477]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">– (aa) Abdomen with distinct bluish luster dorsally.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,948,484,506]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(bb) Female: clypeus with two large lateral creamy white marks (
<figureCitation box="[828,888,484,506]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 2bb).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,965,513,535]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(cc) Male: Head with large subtriangular mark on clypeus. ... 
<taxonomicName box="[795,905,514,535]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[795,905,514,535]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">N. coreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 59
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[151,192,542,564]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,192,542,564]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">3(1)</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(a) Antenna with scape and pedicel usually entirely yellow in both sexes (see 
<figureCitation box="[942,1000,572,594]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 1aa, bb), scape at most with obscure blackish mark. ... 
<taxonomicName box="[324,453,601,623]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridescens">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,453,601,623]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">N. iridescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 59
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[151,1258,631,653]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead box="[151,1258,631,653]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
– (aa) Scape and pedicel mostly black in female (e.g., 
<figureCitation box="[706,765,631,653]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 4aa, bb), at least scape black dorsally in male. ... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1246,1258,631,652]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">4</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[151,191,660,682]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,191,660,682]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">4(3)</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,985,689,711]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(a) Head (
<figureCitation box="[311,371,689,711]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 4a, b), thorax and abdomen richly marked with whitish yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,1120,719,741]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(b) Facial and frontoclypeal crests prominent, sharply carinate (
<figureCitation box="[824,883,719,741]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 4a, b). ... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1980" box="[984,1060,719,740]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satoi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[984,1060,719,740]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">N. satoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 60
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[151,948,748,770]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
– (aa) Head (
<figureCitation box="[311,371,748,770]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 4aa, bb), thorax and abdomen with few pale-yellow marks.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,991,777,799]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(bb) Facial and frontoclypeal crests low, not sharply carinate (
<figureCitation box="[796,856,777,799]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 4aa, bb). ... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[979,991,778,799]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">5</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[151,191,806,828]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,191,806,828]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">5(4)</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,746,836,858]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">(a) Small species, female 7–9.5 mm, male 7.5–8.5 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,1307,865,887]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(b) Head entirely black in both sexes, except for sometimes obscure small spot at upper facial orbit (
<figureCitation box="[1176,1236,865,887]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 5b, c).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,1029,895,917]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(c) Vertex and temple smooth, with shallow distant punctures (
<figureCitation box="[816,876,895,917]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 4aa, bb; 5b, c).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,821,924,946]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">(d) Mesoscutellum and metascutellum entirely black in female.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,767,953,975]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(e) Cell C of forewing pilose all over. ... 
<taxonomicName box="[604,707,953,975]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[604,707,953,975]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">N. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 60
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[151,668,983,1005]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
– (aa) Large species, female 
<quantity box="[461,531,983,1004]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
, male 
<quantity box="[593,663,983,1004]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(bb) Head with large pale yellow mark between antennae in female (
<figureCitation box="[888,951,1012,1034]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 5bb, cc), anterior surface mostly pale yellow in male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,1031,1071,1093]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(cc) Vertex and temple covered with dense, well-separated punctures (
<figureCitation box="[877,937,1071,1093]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1176,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-409@39.[151,1435,1176,1824]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 3. Key to Neurotoma species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876503/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: 5bb, cc).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,801,1100,1122]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">(dd) Mesoscutellum and metascutellum pale yellow in female.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,220,1151]" box="[199,1095,1129,1151]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
(ee) Cell C of forewing glabrous, with some pilosity in apical posterior part. ... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara, Choi &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2018" box="[964,1035,1129,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silla">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[964,1035,1129,1151]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">N. silla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 61
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
</keyStep>
</key>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
